    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-strung S54 3.2L inline-six, equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example utilizes the sought-after 6-speed manual gearbox and a mechanical limited-slip differential. The chassis integrity is preserved through proactive rear subframe reinforcement, and the suspension maintains its signature communicative feedback. While the aesthetic reflects its history as a driven machine, the powertrain remains exceptionally healthy, delivering linear power through the entire 8,000 RPM sweep. A mechanically sound, high-performance icon ready for the canyons.",
